  "texts": [
    "It combines the strengths of the Loewe and Bliss models, allowing for a systematic evaluation of various patterns of drug interaction.",
    "The ZIP score provides a numerical value ranging from -1 to 1, indicating the degree of synergy or antagonism observed in a drug combination.",
    "it is derived from the concept of zero interaction (Sühnel 1992), which assumes that the potency of a drug's dose-response curve remains unaltered when combined with another drug (Yadav et al. 2015).",
    "Highest Single Agent (HSA) model, also known as Gaddum's non-interaction model (Berenbaum, 1989), provides a simple approach to estimate the expected combination effect of multiple drugs.",
    "According to this model, the expected combination effect is determined by taking the difference between the combined response of the drugs E (A,B,C,…,N) and the maximum response observed among the individual drugs max E A, E B, E C, …, E N."
  ],
